This product adapts logic from the following open-source projects. No source
files were copied verbatim; their approaches were reimplemented for Baton's
local, git-only use. Attribution is provided here in good faith.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
handler.dev — Launchable.ai
  https://github.com/Launchable-AI/handler.dev
  License: MIT
  Adapted: git worktree create/list/status/merge/remove logic
           (packages/server/src/services/worktree.ts) and the shell-free
           execFile execution approach (packages/server/src/lib/safe-exec.ts).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
rover — Endor Software Inc.
  https://github.com/endorhq/rover
  License: Apache-2.0
  Adapted: per-task branch-naming + base-commit recording pattern
           (packages/cli/src/lib/task-setup.ts, TaskSetup.initial()).
  Apache-2.0 NOTICE: portions of this product's design are derived from rover,
  Copyright (c) Endor Software Inc., licensed under the Apache License 2.0.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Daintree — daintreehq
  https://github.com/daintreehq/daintree
  License: Apache-2.0
  Adapted: hardened git invocation — per-command timeout, environment
           sanitization, and non-interactive `-c` config flags
           (electron/utils/hardenedGit.ts); worktree create/remove robustness —
           collision-aware branch naming, prune-on-orphan, retry-on-busy, and
           in-progress repo-state detection (electron/workspace-host/
           WorkspaceService.ts); porcelain-v2 conflict parsing + labels
           (electron/services/git/porcelainConflicts.ts).
  Apache-2.0 NOTICE: portions of this product's design are derived from
  Daintree, Copyright (c) 2025-2026 Greg Priday, licensed under the Apache
  License 2.0.

Aider (repo-map)
  https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider
  License: Apache-2.0
  Adapted: concept only, no code — CODEBASE.md's degree-ranked "key symbols"
  section under a token budget follows Aider's tree-sitter + graph-ranked
  repo-map idea (src/kb/codebasemd.ts).

Repomix / llms.txt convention
  https://github.com/yamadashy/repomix (MIT) · https://llmstxt.org/
  Adapted: concept only, no code — packing a curated, AI-friendly markdown
  index of a codebase (CODEBASE.md root index + per-project maps,
  src/kb/codebasemd.ts).

claude-code-router
  https://github.com/musistudio/claude-code-router
  License: MIT
  Adapted: concept only, no code — task-type → agent/model routing config
  shape (baton.config.json), applied at the agent-handoff level instead of an
  API proxy (src/routing.ts).
